</m:msub>
</m:math>
 respectively be the angular speeds of the hour hand of a watch and that of the earth around its own axis. Compare the angular speeds of earth and hour hand of a watch.
</para>
<para id="element-6a"><term>Solution : </term>
The time periods of hour hand and that of the earth are 12 hours and 24 hours respectively. Now,
</para>
